#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-simple-expression-in-memo.md
M|rules|title: Do not wrap a simple expression with a primitive result type in useMemo
M|rules|impact: LOW-MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: wasted computation on every render
M|rules|tags: rerender, useMemo, optimization
M|rules|When an expression is simple (few logical or arithmetical operators) and has a primitive result type (boolean, number, string), do not wrap it in `useMemo`.
M|rules|Calling `useMemo` and comparing hook dependencies may consume more resources than the expression itself.
M|rules|**Incorrect:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Header({ user, notifications }: Props) {
M|rules|const isLoading = useMemo(() => {
M|rules|return user.isLoading || notifications.isLoading
M|rules|}, [user.isLoading, notifications.isLoading])
M|rules|if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />
M|rules|// return some markup
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Header({ user, notifications }: Props) {
M|rules|const isLoading = user.isLoading || notifications.isLoading
M|rules|if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />
M|rules|// return some markup
M|rules|}
M|rules|```